cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the complexity of model checking for LTL formulae, which is a topic closely related to logic.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as LTL is commonly used in AI for specifying temporal properties of systems.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as LTL is used in programming language semantics and verification.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper deals with the complexity of model checking, which is a fundamental algorithmic problem.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as LTL is a formal language used to specify temporal properties of systems.
